commit.message: replace trunk with latest to avoid going back to specifying all versions
remove python3.7 until travis supports it

constrain to requirements.txt and still deps

using -rrequirements.txt gets two versions of django and fails with
"Double requirements" error.
remove python3.3 and add 3.7 to travis list
update psycopg version for pypy{,3} as well to avoid error with postgres10
remove old python versions, add new django versions, unpin test libraries to get tests to pass

upgrade psycopg2 to >=2.7 to handle postgres >=10

psycopg2<2.7 looks for the a postgres version like x.xx which
unfortunately crashes trying to match 10.xx see
https://github.com/psycopg/psycopg2/issues/594
